    "Id": "chassisdef_fusillade_FDE-1A",
    "Name": "Fusillade",
    "Details": "The FDE-1A is one of the most unconventional Capellan designs ever fielded, built around twin Arrow IV artillery systems carrying a staggering variety of munitions. Homing, cluster, Thunder, Inferno and Davy Crockett nuclear rounds give it an answer to virtually any battlefield situation. A torso-mounted cockpit frees the head for an Anti-Missile System and heat sink. Medium Lasers and Small Pulse Lasers handle self-defense, but the Fusillade was never meant to fight at close range.\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Quirk: Stable</color></b>\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Drop Cost Multiplier: 1.09</color></b>\n\n<color=#FFEF00>Arm Actuator Limits: Left Upper, Right Upper</color>",
