  "StockRole": "Heavy Fire Support",
  "YangsThoughts": "Hollis Incorporated built a handful of these for the Capellan Confederation and called it experimental, which is putting it mildly. Two Arrow IV systems with nuclear ammunition aboard is not something most commanders want pointed anywhere near their own forces. The torso cockpit is unusual but it freed up the head for an AMS which makes sense given what it carries. Opponents who knew what it was loaded with sometimes just backed off entirely. Can't really blame them.",
